---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Vote" description="Campaign and manifesto page.">
  <section class="vote-page">
    <section class="pillars">
      <h1><span class="lead-word">Better</span><span class="main-word">Portfolios</span></h1>
      <h1><span class="lead-word">Stronger</span><span class="main-word">Networks</span></h1>
      <h1><span class="lead-word">More</span><span class="main-word">Internships</span></h1>
    </section>

    <section class="candidates">
      <article class="candidate">
        <div class="portrait">
          <img class="portrait-image" src="/images/sebastian-chair.jpg" alt="Sebastian portrait" />
        </div>
        <div class="candidate-heading">
          <h2>MSSA Chair</h2>
          <p class="candidate-name">Sebastian</p>
        </div>
        <div class="candidate-copy manifesto-copy">
          <p>
            Through being leader of MSSA Climate Action Group, as well as creative
            director of MSSA photography, I am confident that I can benefit the role
            of MSSA Chair in every scale, for the individual student, for our community,
            and for how we present ourselves and collaborate with the world beyond the school.
            If you have met me, you know I am outgoing and friendly; always happy to talk
            and help you. As chair, some of my current goals are to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Involve the architecture staff / professors within MSSA subgroups through architecture competitions with students and teachers in teams.</li>
            <li>Give the ability for connectivity through a more rigorous interactive online website.</li>
            <li>Collaborate with cross faculties from both Universities MMU and UoM for inter curricular events specifically with the visual arts faculty and civil engineering faculty.</li>
            <li>Clear information and liaison between what students actually want vs what they are offered in the MSSA.</li>
            <li>Societies made accessible through defined calendars and schedules for friendly tournaments for the sports and clear events and incentives for the students.</li>
            <li>Quantitative outputs that result in verifiable and CV transferable experiences from MSSA to boost student employability.</li>
            <li>Direct relation with companies to boost and fast track active participants of the MSSA for summer or easter architecture internships.</li>
            <li>Greater reach for architecture companies, guest speakers and industry opportunities, for real networking.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Vote for Sebastian for MSSA to experience, grow and perform.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="candidate">
        <div class="portrait">
          <img
            class="portrait-image portrait-image--secretary"
            src="/images/ansh-secretary.jpeg"
            alt="Ansh portrait"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="candidate-heading">
          <h2>MSSA Secretary</h2>
          <p class="candidate-name">Ansh</p>
        </div>
        <div class="candidate-copy">
          <p>
            Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Mauris viverra,
            lacus at faucibus commodo, mi libero pellentesque orci, sed sollicitudin
            lectus lorem id nunc. Quisque dictum consequat nisl, vitae facilisis erat
            lobortis ut. Suspendisse nec semper ipsum. Duis eget sapien sed augue
            tincidunt vestibulum. Curabitur euismod, odio ac tempor vulputate, turpis
            orci vulputate elit, et volutpat augue augue nec massa. Integer lacinia
            tortor non massa laoreet, sed luctus nisl semper. Aenean a mauris nec nunc
            vulputate dictum. Vestibulum ante ipsum primis in faucibus orci luctus et
            ultrices posuere cubilia curae; Nam pellentesque, nisl non mattis ultricies,
            dui odio porttitor erat, eget tincidunt libero sapien sed justo. Aliquam
            bibendum luctus velit, sit amet suscipit augue facilisis vel. Fusce ultrices
            tristique elit, in eleifend erat feugiat ut. Nunc tincidunt sapien in erat
